snippet.textDisplay: Please take the time to research how fast fashion impacts the environment. It's so damaging to support a brand like Primark by doing a gigantic haul and then promoting it to your considerable audience, a large percentage of which are probably young people. Even if you give the stuff to charity it doesn't actually cancel out any of the damage you've already done and tbh feels like an excuse you tell yourself so you don't have to think too hard about social responsibility. Like idk I like giving people the benefit of the doubt and I'm not expecting you to straight up stop buying fast fashion, especially if your income depends on it but have some perspective and consider what's happening in the world atm. Like I hate to sound so harsh but if consumers don't ask for change then companies aren't going to do anything about environmental policy.
